<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Solanum woodii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.74.10159.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/110014" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">4</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Bolivia in the Departments of Chuquisaca and Santa Cruz, growing in Chaco and Chaco forests of inter-Andean valleys, in dry Chaco woodlands on sandy and clay soils near water sources, rivers and in moist depressions in partial or full shade; between 300-1,800 m elevation.
</paragraph>
